field.value:
I had define blockcomponent like this

#blockcomponent(Grid with "source=$users")
  #tablestart
    <table class='outline'>
  #end
  #empty
    <td>User is empty ...</td>
  #end
#end

When there is no data available GridComponent generate the following html:
<table class='outline'>\n		</table><td>User is empty ...</td>\n

I would love to see the empty section render inside the table tag so I modify the Render method:
		public override void Render()
		{
                         ...
			ShowStartTable();
			ShowHeader(source);

			bool hasItems = ShowRows(source);

			if (hasItems == false)
			{
				ShowEmpty();
			}

                       ShowFooter();
                       ShowEndTable();
                       .....
		}

and the ShowEmpty() as
		private void ShowEmpty()
		{
			if (Context.HasSection("empty"))
			{
                                 // detect <td> tag if you care ...
				Context.RenderSection("empty");
			}
			else
			{
				RenderText("<td>Grid has no data</td>");
			}
		}

now the result when empty data:
<table class='outline'>\n <td>User is empty ...</td>\n	</table>
